  {
    "doc_id": "nvidia_2025_q1_earnings_release",
    "title": "NVIDIA Fiscal 2026 First Quarter Earnings Highlights",
    "url": "https://investor.nvidia.com/",
    "source_name": "NVIDIA Investor Relations",
    "language": "en",
    "doc_type": "earnings_release",
    "company": "NVIDIA",
    "symbol": "NVDA",
    "published_at": "2025-05-28",
    "inline_text": "NVIDIA reported fiscal 2026 first quarter revenue of 44.1 billion U.S. dollars, up sharply year over year, driven primarily by data center demand. Data Center revenue reached 39.1 billion U.S. dollars and remained the core growth engine. The company said demand for AI infrastructure and accelerated computing continued to support strong customer spending. Gaming, professional visualization and automotive contributed additional revenue, but the business mix was still dominated by data center products. Management emphasized continued investment in AI systems, networking and platform software while highlighting supply ramp and customer adoption across hyperscalers and enterprises."
  },
  {
    "doc_id": "microsoft_2025_q3_earnings_release",
    "title": "Microsoft Fiscal 2025 Third Quarter Earnings Highlights",
    "url": "https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/",
    "source_name": "Microsoft Investor Relations",
    "language": "en",
    "doc_type": "earnings_release",
    "company": "Microsoft",
    "symbol": "MSFT",
    "published_at": "2025-04-30",
    "inline_text": "Microsoft reported fiscal 2025 third quarter revenue of 70.1 billion U.S. dollars. Microsoft Cloud revenue was 42.4 billion U.S. dollars, reflecting continued enterprise demand for cloud services and AI-related workloads. The company said Azure and other cloud services revenue again grew strongly, supported by capacity expansion and AI adoption. Productivity and Business Processes as well as Intelligent Cloud remained the largest contributors to revenue and operating profit. Management highlighted durable commercial bookings, large customer commitments and ongoing investment in AI infrastructure."
  },
  {
    "doc_id": "amazon_2025_q1_earnings_release",
    "title": "Amazon First Quarter 2025 Earnings Highlights",
    "url": "https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/company-news",
    "source_name": "Amazon News",
    "language": "en",
    "doc_type": "earnings_release",
    "company": "Amazon",
    "symbol": "AMZN",
    "published_at": "2025-05-01",
    "inline_text": "Amazon reported first quarter 2025 net sales of 143.3 billion U.S. dollars, with growth supported by online stores, third-party seller services, advertising and AWS. AWS revenue reached 29.3 billion U.S. dollars and remained Amazon's main profit engine. Operating income improved year over year as fulfillment efficiency and cloud scale supported margins. The company highlighted demand for generative AI services on AWS, continued infrastructure investment and expanding advertising monetization across its consumer ecosystem."
  },
  {
    "doc_id": "alphabet_2025_q1_earnings_release",
    "title": "Alphabet First Quarter 2025 Earnings Highlights",
    "url": "https://abc.xyz/investor/",
    "source_name": "Alphabet Investor Relations",
    "language": "en",
    "doc_type": "earnings_release",
    "company": "Alphabet",
    "symbol": "GOOG",
    "published_at": "2025-04-24",
    "inline_text": "Alphabet reported first quarter 2025 revenue of 90.2 billion U.S. dollars. Google Search and other advertising businesses remained the largest revenue contributor, while Google Cloud continued to expand with stronger profitability. The company said cloud demand was driven by data analytics, infrastructure and AI products. Operating margin improved year over year as cost discipline and scale benefits supported earnings. Management also highlighted ongoing capital expenditure to support AI infrastructure and product innovation."
  }
]
